<div hidden
     class="fixed inset-0 z-50 opacity-0 pointer-events-none transition-opacity duration-200"
     data-controller="modal"
     data-modal-auto-open-value="true"
     data-action="click->modal#backdropClick keydown@window->modal#escape open-modal@window->modal#open">
  <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-black/50 dark:bg-black/70"></div>
  <div class="relative flex items-center justify-center min-h-full p-4">
    <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900 rounded-xl shadow-2xl w-full max-w-xl max-h-[85dvh] flex flex-col border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 relative"
         data-modal-target="panel">

      <button data-action="click->modal#close"
              class="absolute top-3 right-3 z-10 w-7 h-7 flex items-center justify-center rounded-md hover:bg-gray-100 dark:hover:bg-gray-800 text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 cursor-pointer text-lg leading-none">✕</button>

      <div class="overflow-y-auto px-5 pt-8 pb-4 space-y-6 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 font-serif">

        <div class="flex flex-col items-center gap-3 text-center">
          <%= image_tag 'icon.png', class: 'w-16 h-16 rounded-2xl shadow-sm', alt: 'Finesse Chat' %>
          <p class="text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">
          This microapp was <a href="https://github.com/scudco/finesse" target="_blank" class="underline font-semibold text-teal-600 dark:text-teal-400 hover:text-teal-500 dark:hover:text-teal-300">built with Finesse</a> by <a href="https://adam.scud.co" target="_blank" class="underline hover:opacity-75">Adam</a> to demonstrate the practical differences between
          <span class="text-blue-600">Polling</span>,
          <span class="text-amber-500">WebSockets</span>,
          and
          <span class="text-teal-600">Server-Sent Events</span>.
          </p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400 dark:text-gray-500">powered by Rails 8 and Hotwire</p>
        </div>

        <section>
          <h3 class="font-semibold font-sans text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-100 mb-2">Three Timely Transports</h3>
          <div class="space-y-2">
            <div class="rounded-lg border border-blue-200 dark:border-blue-800 bg-blue-50 dark:bg-blue-950/40 px-3 py-2 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">
              <p class="mb-2"><span class="text-blue-600">Polling</span> will perform a regular old fetch every 7.77 seconds to get the latest messages. It is the simplest approach to updating data. Very reliable, but definitely not real-time.</p>
              <p>In this app, <span class="text-blue-600">Polling</span> is not used as a fallback for <span class="text-amber-500">WebSockets</span> or <span class="text-teal-600">Server-Sent Events</span> so that those features' limitations are more clear. In a real app, you'd likely want polling always on to sync to server state.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="rounded-lg border border-amber-200 dark:border-amber-800 bg-amber-50 dark:bg-amber-950/40 px-3 py-2 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300"><span class="text-amber-500">WebSockets</span> via SolidCable is available in Rails 8 without any real configuration needed. It is, however, more finicky when dealing with ordered data and reconnects. This was the fastest but least reliable transport in my testing.</div>
            <div class="rounded-lg border border-teal-200 dark:border-teal-800 bg-teal-50 dark:bg-teal-950/40 px-3 py-2 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300"><span class="text-teal-600">Server-Sent Events</span> being a long-lived HTTP connection means browsers work well with it by default. This app demonstrates its reliability and speed compared to WebSockets.</div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h3 class="font-semibold font-sans text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-100 mb-2">The Big Red Button</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mb-2">
            Inside the app, the Bot Storm button will fire a burst of messages from bots to demonstrate how each transport handles message flooding.
          </p>
          <button class="btn-storm w-full mb-3 pointer-events-none select-none justify-center text-sm py-2" tabindex="-1" aria-hidden="true">
            <span class="bolt-zap">⚡</span> Bot Storm
          </button>
          <p class="text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mb-2">
            When using <span class="text-amber-500">WebSockets</span>, you can expect to see messages tagged with an <span class="font-sans inline-block px-1 py-0.5 rounded text-xs font-semibold bg-amber-400/20 text-amber-700 dark:text-amber-400 border border-amber-300 dark:border-amber-600">OUT OF ORDER</span> badge. This demonstrates that WebSockets messages have a decent potential of being received out of order.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h3 class="font-semibold font-sans text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-100 mb-2">Things To Know and Do During Your Stay</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-1.5 list-disc list-inside">
            <li>The chat resets every five minutes — the channel name rotates on each reset</li>
            <li>Most markdown is supported — **bold**, `code`, *italic*, and more</li>
            <li>Press <kbd class="font-sans px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800 font-mono text-xs">↑</kbd> in the empty input to edit your last message</li>
            <li>Hover one of your messages to reveal edit/delete controls</li>
            <li>Click the ↺ icon next to your username to get a new random username</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h3 class="font-semibold font-sans text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-100 mb-2">Secret Hacker Commands</h3>
          <dl class="space-y-1.5">
            <div class="flex gap-2">
              <dt class="font-mono text-teal-600 dark:text-teal-400 shrink-0 w-32">/help</dt>
              <dd>Show a list of commands in chat</dd>
            </div>
            <div class="flex gap-2">
              <dt class="font-mono text-teal-600 dark:text-teal-400 shrink-0 w-32">/time</dt>
              <dd>Post the current server time</dd>
            </div>
            <div class="flex gap-2">
              <dt class="font-mono text-teal-600 dark:text-teal-400 shrink-0 w-32">/meow, /🐱</dt>
              <dd>Thanks for signing up for Cat Facts!</dd>
            </div>
            <div class="flex gap-2">
              <dt class="font-mono text-teal-600 dark:text-teal-400 shrink-0 w-32">/woof, /🐶</dt>
              <dd>Dog Facts for the refined factician</dd>
            </div>
            <div class="flex gap-2">
              <dt class="font-mono text-teal-600 dark:text-teal-400 shrink-0 w-32">/wut &lt;acronym&gt;</dt>
              <dd>Expand a tech acronym</dd>
            </div>
            <div class="flex gap-2">
              <dt class="font-mono text-teal-600 dark:text-teal-400 shrink-0 w-32">/me &lt;action&gt;</dt>
              <dd>Post a third-person action</dd>
            </div>
          </dl>
        </section>

      </div>

      <div class="px-5 py-3 border-t border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 shrink-0 flex flex-col gap-3">
        <a href="https://github.com/scudco/finesse.chat" target="_blank"
           class="flex items-center justify-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 hover:bg-gray-50 dark:hover:bg-gray-800 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 text-xs font-medium transition-colors">
          <svg class="w-4 h-4" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="currentColor"><path d="M8 0C3.58 0 0 3.58 0 8c0 3.54 2.29 6.53 5.47 7.59.4.07.55-.17.55-.38 0-.19-.01-.82-.01-1.49-2.01.37-2.53-.49-2.69-.94-.09-.23-.48-.94-.82-1.13-.28-.15-.68-.52-.01-.53.63-.01 1.08.58 1.23.82.72 1.21 1.87.87 2.33.66.07-.52.28-.87.51-1.07-1.78-.2-3.64-.89-3.64-3.95 0-.87.31-1.59.82-2.15-.08-.2-.36-1.02.08-2.12 0 0 .67-.21 2.2.82.64-.18 1.32-.27 2-.27s1.36.09 2 .27c1.53-1.04 2.2-.82 2.2-.82.44 1.1.16 1.92.08 2.12.51.56.82 1.27.82 2.15 0 3.07-1.87 3.75-3.65 3.95.29.25.54.73.54 1.48 0 1.07-.01 1.93-.01 2.2 0 .21.15.46.55.38A8.01 8.01 0 0016 8c0-4.42-3.58-8-8-8z"/></svg>
          scudco/finesse.chat
        </a>
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4">
          <label class="flex items-center gap-2 text-xs text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 cursor-pointer select-none">
            <input type="checkbox" checked
                   class="w-3.5 h-3.5 rounded accent-teal-600 cursor-pointer"
                   data-modal-target="showOnLaunch"
                   data-action="change->modal#toggleShowOnLaunch">
            Show on launch
          </label>
          <button data-action="click->modal#close"
                  class="px-4 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-teal-600 hover:bg-teal-500 text-white text-xs font-semibold transition-colors cursor-pointer">
            Start chatting
          </button>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
